      "side": 1,
      "message": "Line 125: RTT baseline is the average of the first five non-zero samples and is never refreshed. If the call starts on a temporarily bad path, later RTT congestion is underdetected; if it starts unusually low, normal path changes can be treated as congestion. Use a slowly adapting minimum/low-percentile baseline, or reset the baseline after network changes/encoder restart so congestion scoring remains representative.\n```suggestion\n    if (rttMs \u003e 0) {\n        if (baselineRtt_ \u003d\u003d 0.0f)\n            baselineRtt_ \u003d rttMs;\n        else\n            baselineRtt_ \u003d std::min(baselineRtt_ * 0.995f + rttMs * 0.005f, rttMs);\n    }\n```",
      "revId": "cda1fd7c9170b4c03c12fd152e96e4bf2b0c3dd9",
      "serverId": "1e26b4c1-6b8c-47ff-9df7-501b633d3b5a"
    },
