      "writtenOn": "2026-05-31T14:33:21Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Line 148: The computed congestion decrease is much more aggressive than the old loss controller for moderate loss. With the defaults, a congestion score just above the 0.08 threshold can immediately reduce video by about 4%, while 10% loss reduces by ~35%; the previous logic used packetLoss / 150, so 10% loss reduced ~6.7%. This risks visible quality oscillation, especially with the RTCP polling interval shortened to 2 seconds. Consider bounding the first decrease step or tuning the default maxDecreaseFactor/loss scale to preserve comparable behavior unless measurements justify the larger drop.\n```suggestion\n    float factor \u003d 1.0f - congestion * cfg_.maxDecreaseFactor;\n    factor \u003d std::clamp(factor, 0.75f, 0.95f);\n```",
      "revId": "cda1fd7c9170b4c03c12fd152e96e4bf2b0c3dd9",
      "serverId": "1e26b4c1-6b8c-47ff-9df7-501b633d3b5a"
    },
