      "side": 1,
      "message": "Line 144: targetBitrate_ and lastStableBitrate_ are left without in-class initializers and rely on every constructor delegating through the Config constructor. That is currently true, but this class is stateful and easy to extend incorrectly. Initializing them in the declaration makes the invariant explicit and prevents accidental uninitialized reads if another constructor is added.\n```suggestion\n    unsigned targetBitrate_ {Config {}.initialBitrateKbps};\n    unsigned lastStableBitrate_ {Config {}.initialBitrateKbps};\n```",
      "revId": "cda1fd7c9170b4c03c12fd152e96e4bf2b0c3dd9",
